description:
Bernell Trammell, a black man from Milwaukee was shot and killed in front of his own business for holding a “vote for Trump” sign. His murderer is still on the loose. 

He did nothing wrong. Another innocent life lost. Yet, I see NO posts about his black life mattering. I see no outrage. I see no celebrities screaming for his justice. Why? Is it because he was a conservative black man? And those lives don’t matter? 

Because last I checked, ALL BLACK LIVES MATTER.

Say his name. Say it with me. He mattered.
